message.content:
A whale is a large marine mammal that belongs to the order Cetacea.
It has a streamlined body with a fusiform shape and a tail fin called fluke.
Whales have a slick and smooth skin that is usually dark gray or black in color.
Their bodies are extremely large, and they can grow up to 100 feet long, depending on the species.
Whales are commonly found in the ocean, but some species like beluga whales inhabit freshwater rivers.
They have a blowhole on top of their head, which they use to breathe air.
Whales are intelligent animals that communicate with each other through sounds and songs.
